# Path to Ableton Live's Extension Host, used by `npm start` to run this
# extension in a live-reloading dev host without restarting Live each time.
#
# How to find the correct path:
#   - macOS: point at the Live app bundle itself, e.g.
#       EXTENSION_HOST_PATH="/Applications/Ableton Live 12 Suite.app"
#   - Windows: point at the Live install root or Live.exe, e.g.
#       EXTENSION_HOST_PATH="C:\ProgramData\Ableton\Live 12 Suite\Program\Live.exe"
#   - Alternatively, on either platform, you can point directly at the
#     ExtensionHostNodeModule.node file itself:
#       macOS:   .../Ableton Live 12 Suite.app/Contents/Helpers/ExtensionHost/ExtensionHostNodeModule.node
#       Windows: ...\Ableton Live 12 Suite\Program\ExtensionHost\ExtensionHostNodeModule.node
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and update the path below to match your local
# Ableton Live installation (version/edition name may differ, e.g.
# "Ableton Live 12 Suite.app" vs "Ableton Live 12 Beta.app").
EXTENSION_HOST_PATH="/Applications/Ableton Live 12 Suite.app"
